text: The crab-eating macaque (Macaca fascicularis) is a monkey. It is mostly native to Southeast Asia. It is also called the cynomolgus monkey, Philippine monkey, and the long-tailed macaque. In 2018, scientists in China cloned the crab- eating macaque. They named the two baby monkeys Zhong Zhong and Hua Hua. ==References== Category:Mammals of Asia Category:Old World monkeys
title: Crab-eating Macaque
